A work item is one piece of work that needs to be tracked.

It is used to track things like features, requirements, bugs, code defects, project issues, and risks



Work Item Types

  Epic

    An Epic is a very large goal. Azure Boards is basically a project tracking board.

  Feature

    A Feature is a big part of an Epic. Azure Boards uses Features to break a very large goal into smaller sections.


  User Story

    A User Story explains something the user needs. A User Story is a small goal written from the user’s point of view.

  Task

    A Task is a smaller job that helps complete a User Story. A Task is the actual work someone does to complete a User Story.

  Bug

    A Bug is something broken in the app. A Bug is something broken or not working correctly in the project.




Example

Epic: Build a Map App

  Feature: Add an Interactive Map

    User Story: As a user, I want to click a marker and see more information

      Task: Create the marker
      Task: Add a click event
      Task: Create the popup box
      Task: Show information inside the popup
      Task: Test that the popup works

      Bug: Marker popup does not open when clicked


    User Story: As a user, I want to zoom in and out of the map

      Task: Add zoom controls
      Task: Make sure zoom works with the mouse
      Task: Test zoom on different browsers

      Bug: Map zoom freezes sometimes


  Feature: Add a Search Bar

    User Story: As a user, I want to search for a location

      Task: Create the search input
      Task: Add a search button
      Task: Connect search to map locations
      Task: Move the map to the searched location

      Bug: Search bar gives the wrong location


  Feature: Improve Map Performance

    User Story: As a user, I want the map to load quickly

      Task: Reduce unnecessary map data
      Task: Optimize marker loading
      Task: Test map speed

      Bug: Map loads too slowly


Hierarchy

Epic: Build user account system
 └── Feature: Login and signup
      └── User Story: User can log into account
           └── Task: Create login form
           └── Task: Validate password
           └── Bug: Login button does not work







A work item form usually has important fields like:

  Title: The Title is the name of the work item.
  
  Assigned To: Assigned To shows who is responsible for the work
  
  State: State shows the current progress of the work item.
  
  Reason: Reason explains why the work item is in its current state.
  
  Area: Area tells what part of the project the work belongs to.
  
  Iteration: Iteration usually means the sprint or time period for the work.
  





















































